Package com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.common

This package provides functionality shared by examples.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ResponseCallback
    Callback used for processing a response message.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChannelSession
    Manages UPA channel and provides methods for connection establishment, channel initialization, read, and write methods for Consumer and NIProvider example applications.
    DictionaryHandler
    This is the dictionary handler for the UPA consumer application.
    DirectoryHandler
    This is the source directory handler for the UPA consumer application.
    GenericResponseStatusFlags
    Status flags used by the UPA Java Generic Consumer and Provider applications.
    LoginHandler
    This is the Login handler for the UPA Consumer and NIProvider application.
    NIProviderDictionaryHandler
    This is the dictionary handler for the UPA consumer application.
    ProviderDictionaryHandler
    This is the dictionary handler for both the UPA - Java Interactive Provider application.
    ProviderLoginHandler
    This is the implementation of processing of login requests and login status messages.
    StreamIdWatchList
    This is a hash map based WatchList for quick lookup of item states when response is received.
    StreamIdWatchList.StreamIdKey  
    StreamIdWatchList.WatchListEntry
    Watch list entry used by StreamIdWatchList.
    SymbolListHandler
    This is the symbol list handler for the UPA consumer application.
    UnSupportedMsgHandler
    This is the implementation of sending unsupported status message for the interactive provider and generic provider applications.
